Today I have received my Master of Education degree, a journey that would not have been possible without the unwavering support of all those around me. Specifically, to my favorite teacher of all time, Mr. Foust. In high school, Foust was my art teacher and his impact on my life cannot be overstated. Thanks to his guidance, I was able to gain admission to the School of Visual Arts. Foust again played a pivotal role in my life when in 2017, he asked me to take his place upon his retirement at our high school Notre Dame Academy. While I couldn't accept his offer at the time, it was and still is the greatest honor of my life. It ignited a spark in me that I have not been able to shake. I began to imagine a future (somewhere along the line) as an art teacher of some kind, with a hope to impact my students’ lives in the same way he has impacted mine. While pursuing modeling, I have always felt like a part of me was abandoning my artistic roots. However, as time passed, I came to realize the true value of Foust’s teachings - art is everywhere, it is a part of us. It’s the videos I create, the way I choose to express myself, it is all art. 

I must also acknowledge the support of my mother, who has always encouraged me to follow my passions and value education. It was thanks to her, that I found Grand Canyon University, an online Master of Education program that I could complete from anywhere. Although the journey was stressful at times (United’s Wi-Fi can use a serious upgrade), I am grateful to have had my best friend Christina by my side too. Together, we have now achieved our Master of Education degrees. I am truly grateful to everyone who has helped me along the way and I hope to pay it forward in the years to come! 
👩🏼‍🎓✨🎨

(Check out stevefoust.com)
